ussion of the DNA model\u00e2\u0080\u0099s scientific details", "Occasional unsupported assertions (e.g. male smoking rates)", "Repetition in the analysis of entrenched beliefs leading to minor lack of focus"], "calculationMethod": "Holistic AI evaluation: The student\u00e2\u0080\u0099s exhibition aligns squarely with the 5\u00e2\u0080\u00936 band: three well-contextualized objects are clearly identified, each is explicitly linked to the prompt, and justifications draw on credible evidence. While the discussion of the DNA model blurs historical and conceptual details and a few claims lack full support, the overall coherence, sourcing and clarity justify awarding the top mark of the 5\u00e2\u0080\u00936 band. Given the official total of 6 and the relative strengths and minor weaknesses noted, a final score of 6 accurately reflects the quality of the submission.", "groupName": "TOK Exhibition"}], "strandSelections": [{"versionId": "85df2675-f7bc-4a7a-aa69-718fb002d3a2", "strandId": "17a30166-bc52-427b-904b-44efbdd5c7d7", "selectedBandId": "bd39c308-b52c-4662-b0f5-64d285be9e95", "bandScore": 6, "reasoning": "$49"}], "annotations": [{"id": "92f8f66f-5886-4245-b37c-65f79483bdff", "versionId": "85df2675-f7bc-4a7a-aa69-718fb002d3a2", "criterionId": null, "strandId": null, "type": "weakness", "pageNumber": 1, "bbox": {"x": 0.0918, "y": 0.0788, "width": 0.5308, "height": 0.01780000000000001}, "polygon": [{"x": 0.0918, "y": 0.0788}, {"x": 0.6226, "y": 0.0788}, {"x": 0.6226, "y": 0.0966}, {"x": 0.0918, "y": 0.0966}], "comment": "The research question is stated as a prompt rather than reframed as a knowledge question. The student should articulate a clear TOK knowledge question using terms like \u00e2\u0080\u009cbelief revision\u00e2\u0080\u009d or \u00e2\u0080\u009cvalue change\u00e2\u0080\u009d to ground the exhibition firmly in TOK concepts.", "color": null, "status": "unread", "statusUpdatedAt": null, "statusUpdatedBy": null, "groupName": null}, {"id": "ac7bfe19-fe6a-4cc1-9cc1-a3149ed174cb", "versionId": "85df2675-f7bc-4a7a-aa69-718fb002d3a2", "criterionId": null, "strandId": null, "type": "weakness", "pageNumber": 4, "bbox": {"x": 0.0906, "y": 0.0788, "width": 0.832, "height": 0.085}, "polygon": [{"x": 0.0906, "y": 0.0788}, {"x": 0.9226, "y": 0.0788}, {"x": 0.9226, "y": 0.1638}, {"x": 0.0906, "y": 0.1638}], "comment": "This description of the backfire effect correctly outlines the phenomenon but does not evaluate the original study\u00e2\u0080\u0099s methodology or limitations. The student should discuss sample size, partisan context and how these affect the generalizability of findings.", "color": null, "status": "unread", "statusUpdatedAt": null, "statusUpdatedBy": null, "groupName": null}, {"id": "3cc96bb5-e23b-46d2-a293-84d2b8ac79f1", "versionId": "85df2675-f7bc-4a7a-aa69-718fb002d3a2", "criterionId": null, "strandId": null, "type": "weakness", "pageNumber": 1, "bbox": {"x": 0.0906, "y": 0.5957, "width": 0.8283, "height": 0.2881}, "polygon": [{"x": 0.0906, "y": 0.5957}, {"x": 0.9189, "y": 0.5957}, {"x": 0.9189, "y": 0.8838}, {"x": 0.0906, "y": 0.8838}], "comment": "The claim \u00e2\u0080\u009cOne possible explanation could be\u00e2\u0080\u00a6\u00e2\u0080\u009d is speculative. To improve, ground this hypothesis in scholarly evidence or theory (e.g. studies of advertising influence) and relate it back to how new knowledge confronts existing values.", "color": null, "status": "unread", "statusUpdatedAt": null, "statusUpdatedBy": null, "groupName": null}, {"id": "dae4a251-9878-409f-bf75-fb19a26fe55a", "versionId": "85df2675-f7bc-4a7a-aa69-718fb002d3a2", "criterionId": null, "strandId": null, "type": "weakness", "pageNumber": 1, "bbox": {"x": 0.0906, "y": 0.5957, "width": 0.8283, "height": 0.2881}, "polygon": [{"x": 0.0906, "y": 0.5957}, {"x": 0.9189, "y": 0.5957}, {"x": 0.9189, "y": 0.8838}, {"x": 0.0906, "y": 0.8838}], "comment": "Statistics on smoking trends are presented without evaluating source reliability or considering sampling bias. The student must interrogate the data\u00e2\u0080\u0099s context (e.g. demographics, methodology) and explain how such knowledge shapes or fails to shape beliefs.", "color": null, "status": "unread", "statusUpdatedAt": null, "statusUpdatedBy": null, "groupName": null}, {"id": "c683191c-83db-4bad-888d-5f93211ac251", "versionId": "85df2675-f7bc-4a7a-aa69-718fb002d3a2", "criterionId": null, "strandId": null, "type": "weakness", "pageNumber": 2, "bbox": {"x": 0.0906, "y": 0.415, "width": 0.361, "height": 0.018699999999999994}, "polygon": [{"x": 0.0906, "y": 0.415}, {"x": 0.4516, "y": 0.415}, {"x": 0.4516, "y": 0.4337}, {"x": 0.0906, "y": 0.4337}], "comment": "The header for Object 2 names the DNA model but omits a clear real-world context (e.g. the original laboratory or publication). Including specific historical details would situate the object in its knowledge-production environment.", "color": null, "status": "unread", "statusUpdatedAt": null, "statusUpdatedBy": null, "groupName": null}, {"id": "ff2814d7-fd39-419e-95eb-4e0165027dac", "versionId": "85df2675-f7bc-4a7a-aa69-718fb002d3a2", "criterionId": null, "strandId": null, "type": "weakness", "pageNumber": 2, "bbox": {"x": 0.0906, "y": 0.6118, "width": 0.8308, "height": 0.2551}, "polygon": [{"x": 0.0906, "y": 0.6118}, {"x": 0.9214, "y": 0.6118}, {"x": 0.9214, "y": 0.8669}, {"x": 0.0906, "y": 0.8669}], "comment": "Discussion of A-DNA and Z-DNA is factually informative but lacks precision in chronology and significance. A clearer timeline and explanation of how each discovery shifted scientific beliefs would strengthen the link to changing values.", "color": null, "status": "unread", "statusUpdatedAt": null, "statusUpdatedBy": null, "groupName": null}, {"id": "caa69e56-8d6b-4ddb-ae0d-3d405e15048d", "versionId": "85df2675-f7bc-4a7a-aa69-718fb002d3a2", "criterionId": null, "strandId": null, "type": "weakness", "pageNumber": 1, "bbox": {"x": 0.0969, "y": 0.1817, "width": 0.271, "height": 0.1932}, "polygon": [{"x": 0.0969, "y": 0.1817}, {"x": 0.3679, "y": 0.1817}, {"x": 0.3679, "y": 0.3749}, {"x": 0.0969, "y": 0.3749}], "comment": "The image is described clearly but lacks analysis of how its visual rhetoric shaped 1960s values about smoking. To strengthen the link to the prompt, discuss how the poster\u00e2\u0080\u0099s design influenced beliefs and why it persisted despite harmful knowledge.", "color": null, "status": "unread", "statusUpdatedAt": null, "statusUpdatedBy": null, "groupName": null}, {"id": "f39fcb6b-445f-4fae-86e9-4c45cab8f11f", "versionId": "85df2675-f7bc-4a7a-aa69-718fb002d3a2", "criterionId": null, "strandId": null, "type": "weakness", "pageNumber": 2, "bbox": {"x": 0.0906, "y": 0.6118, "width": 0.8308, "height": 0.2551}, "polygon": [{"x": 0.0906, "y": 0.6118}, {"x": 0.9214, "y": 0.6118}, {"x": 0.9214, "y": 0.8669}, {"x": 0.0906, "y": 0.8669}], "comment": "The justification focuses on personal interest rather than the prompt. The student must explain how the DNA model altered established beliefs about heredity and values around nature versus nurture, linking directly to TOK themes.", "color": null, "status": "unread", "statusUpdatedAt": null, "statusUpdatedBy": null, "groupName": null}, {"id": "0b736548-9be9-4376-b97b-6a3a7487ecd5", "versionId": "85df2675-f7bc-4a7a-aa69-718fb002d3a2", "criterionId": null, "strandId": null, "type": "weakness", "pageNumber": 1, "bbox": {"x": 0.0906, "y": 0.3936, "width": 0.8213, "height": 0.187}, "polygon": [{"x": 0.0906, "y": 0.3936}, {"x": 0.9119, "y": 0.3936}, {"x": 0.9119, "y": 0.5806}, {"x": 0.0906, "y": 0.5806}], "comment": "This description merely outlines the object\u00e2\u0080\u0099s purpose. The student should explicitly connect this to the prompt by explaining how new health research conflicted with entrenched social beliefs and why those beliefs remained resilient.", "color": null, "status": "unread", "statusUpdatedAt": null, "statusUpdatedBy": null, "groupName": null}, {"id": "f1fea7cb-1eda-4635-a1ea-d7f21901e1bc", "versionId": "85df2675-f7bc-4a7a-aa69-718fb002d3a2", "criterionId": null, "strandId": null, "type": "weakness", "pageNumber": 1, "bbox": {"x": 0.0918, "y": 0.1456, "width": 0.42390000000000005, "height": 0.018199999999999994}, "polygon": [{"x": 0.0918, "y": 0.1456}, {"x": 0.5157, "y": 0.1456}, {"x": 0.5157, "y": 0.1638}, {"x": 0.0918, "y": 0.1638}], "comment": "The object header identifies the poster but omits specific real-world context such as publication venue, target audience or historical moment. Precise contextual details would clarify why this object exemplifies conflicts between new knowledge and established values.", "color": null, "status": "unread", "statusUpdatedAt": null, "statusUpdatedBy": null, "groupName": null}, {"id": "a3632b20-1e51-41ad-bc1c-bcc79417777c", "versionId": "85df2675-f7bc-4a7a-aa69-718fb002d3a2", "criterionId": null, "strandId": null, "type": "weakness", "pageNumber": 2, "bbox": {"x": 0.0906, "y": 0.2146, "width": 0.8182, "height": 0.1523}, "polygon": [{"x": 0.0906, "y": 0.2146}, {"x": 0.9088, "y": 0.2146}, {"x": 0.9088, "y": 0.3669}, {"x": 0.0906, "y": 0.3669}], "comment": "The conclusion about demographic differences rephrases earlier points without deepening the TOK analysis. The student should explore factors such as cultural norms or epistemic communities to explain why new knowledge had uneven impact.", "color": null, "status": "unread", "statusUpdatedAt": null, "statusUpdatedBy": null, "groupName": null}, {"id": "9b43af89-345f-49d2-b5f1-487e57e45ceb", "versionId": "85df2675-f7bc-4a7a-aa69-718fb002d3a2", "criterionId": null, "strandId": null, "type": "weakness", "pageNumber": 2, "bbox": {"x": 0.1195, "y": 0.4497, "width": 0.4704, "height": 0.11130000000000007}, "polygon": [{"x": 0.1195, "y": 0.4497}, {"x": 0.5899, "y": 0.4497}, {"x": 0.5899, "y": 0.561}, {"x": 0.1195, "y": 0.561}], "comment": "The image is credited properly but lacks reflection on how the model\u00e2\u0080\u0099s material form and display (e.g. museum exhibit) influences perceptions of scientific authority and shapes belief in genetic determinism.", "color": null, "status": "unread", "statusUpdatedAt": null, "statusUpdatedBy": null, "groupName": null}, {"id": "869d11f7-8115-4a67-a3fb-4a53059354b6", "versionId": "85df2675-f7bc-4a7a-aa69-718fb002d3a2", "criterionId": null, "strandId": null, "type": "weakness", "pageNumber": 2, "bbox": {"x": 0.0906, "y": 0.0788, "width": 0.8251, "height": 0.1198}, "polygon": [{"x": 0.0906, "y": 0.0788}, {"x": 0.9157, "y": 0.0788}, {"x": 0.9157, "y": 0.1986}, {"x": 0.0906, "y": 0.1986}], "comment": "This analysis of male smoking identity touches on social factors but needs to invoke TOK concepts (e.g. shared vs personal knowledge) and explicitly link how new scientific findings challenge or fail to challenge identity-driven beliefs.", "color": null, "status": "unread", "statusUpdatedAt": null, "statusUpdatedBy": null, "groupName": null}, {"id": "10a315a3-f7fb-4ba2-a5a0-35ec9beee68b", "versionId": "85df2675-f7bc-4a7a-aa69-718fb002d3a2", "criterionId": null, "strandId": null, "type": "weakness", "pageNumber": 3, "bbox": {"x": 0.0906, "y": 0.5837, "width": 0.5484, "height": 0.018299999999999983}, "polygon": [{"x": 0.0906, "y": 0.5837}, {"x": 0.639, "y": 0.5837}, {"x": 0.639, "y": 0.602}, {"x": 0.0906, "y": 0.602}], "comment": "The header for Object 3 names the study but does not specify its publication context or audience. Identifying the original academic journal or social media reach would clarify how the backfire effect knowledge circulated and impacted beliefs.", "color": null, "status": "unread", "statusUpdatedAt": null, "statusUpdatedBy": null, "groupName": null}, {"id": "03089f28-9580-41f6-a5e9-d8a496a13ac6", "versionId": "85df2675-f7bc-4a7a-aa69-718fb002d3a2", "criterionId": null, "strandId": null, "type": "weakness", "pageNumber": 3, "bbox": {"x": 0.0906, "y": 0.8268, "width": 0.8138, "height": 0.08589999999999998}, "polygon": [{"x": 0.0906, "y": 0.8268}, {"x": 0.9044, "y": 0.8268}, {"x": 0.9044, "y": 0.9127}, {"x": 0.0906, "y": 0.9127}], "comment": "The initial justification is truncated and lacks depth. The student must complete the thought on participants\u00e2\u0080\u0099 reactions, then connect this evidence to the TOK question about belief persistence versus change.", "color": null, "status": "unread", "statusUpdatedAt": null, "statusUpdatedBy": null, "groupName": null}, {"id": "2052bf98-8656-458a-80ba-efe6594bc5ba", "versionId": "85df2675-f7bc-4a7a-aa69-718fb002d3a2", "criterionId": null, "strandId": null, "type": "weakness", "pageNumber": 3, "bbox": {"x": 0.0906, "y": 0.0788, "width": 0.827, "height": 0.45500000000000007}, "polygon": [{"x": 0.0906, "y": 0.0788}, {"x": 0.9176, "y": 0.0788}, {"x": 0.9176, "y": 0.5338}, {"x": 0.0906, "y": 0.5338}], "comment": "This paragraph describes epigenetics well but reads as scientific summary. To meet the prompt, the student should analyze how this knowledge challenged the value of genetic determinism and provoked shifts in ethical or societal beliefs.", "color": null, "status": "unread", "statusUpdatedAt": null, "statusUpdatedBy": null, "groupName": null}, {"id": "2670e7f1-ce56-42d5-b485-cd48eaeef0c0", "versionId": "85df2675-f7bc-4a7a-aa69-718fb002d3a2", "criterionId": null, "strandId": null, "type": "weakness", "pageNumber": 4, "bbox": {"x": 0.0906, "y": 0.1808, "width": 0.8289, "height": 0.4212}, "polygon": [{"x": 0.0906, "y": 0.1808}, {"x": 0.9195, "y": 0.1808}, {"x": 0.9195, "y": 0.602}, {"x": 0.0906, "y": 0.602}], "comment": "While the student cites examples on WMDs and vaccines, they miss an opportunity to analyze how emotional and cognitive biases operate as ways of knowing in TOK. Explicitly reference concepts like confirmation bias or affective fallacy.", "color": null, "status": "unread", "statusUpdatedAt": null, "statusUpdatedBy": null, "groupName": null}, {"id": "bd25fbd8-bd0d-488f-aab1-7a97fd198c1f", "versionId": "85df2675-f7bc-4a7a-aa69-718fb002d3a2", "criterionId": null, "strandId": null, "type": "weakness", "pageNumber": 4, "bbox": {"x": 0.0906, "y": 0.6167, "width": 0.832, "height": 0.11929999999999996}, "polygon": [{"x": 0.0906, "y": 0.6167}, {"x": 0.9226, "y": 0.6167}, {"x": 0.9226, "y": 0.736}, {"x": 0.0906, "y": 0.736}], "comment": "The conclusion restates earlier points but lacks forward\u00e2\u0080\u0090looking insight. The student could propose how combining rational argument with emotional understanding might better facilitate belief change, linking to TOK notions of empathy in knowledge.", "color": null, "status": "unread", "statusUpdatedAt": null, "statusUpdatedBy": null, "groupName": null}, {"id": "888f76a0-62f0-4123-85f4-4576e8acaf7d", "versionId": "85df2675-f7bc-4a7a-aa69-718fb002d3a2", "criterionId": null, "strandId": null, "type": "weakness", "pageNumber": 3, "bbox": {"x": 0.0956, "y": 0.6158, "width": 0.6358, "height": 0.19189999999999996}, "polygon": [{"x": 0.0956, "y": 0.6158}, {"x": 0.7314, "y": 0.6158}, {"x": 0.7314, "y": 0.8077}, {"x": 0.0956, "y": 0.8077}], "comment": "The screenshot indicates a popular\u00e2\u0080\u0090press source. The student should critique how the medium (JSTOR Daily) affects credibility and examine whether secondary presentation alters the reception of knowledge among different audiences.", "color": null, "status": "unread", "statusUpdatedAt": null, "statusUpdatedBy": null, "groupName": null}, {"id": "78acf493-c58b-4108-a4b7-12fdf9861f2c", "versionId": "85df2675-f7bc-4a7a-aa69-718fb002d3a2", "criterionId": null, "strandId": null, "type": "weakness", "pageNumber": 1, "bbox": {"x": 0.0906, "y": 0.5957, "width": 0.8283, "height": 0.2881}, "polygon": [{"x": 0.0906, "y": 0.5957}, {"x": 0.9189, "y": 0.5957}, {"x": 0.9189, "y": 0.8838}, {"x": 0.0906, "y": 0.8838}], "comment": "The paragraph ends with a comma, indicating an incomplete sentence or thought. Ensure all arguments are fully expressed; an unfinished statement undermines clarity and coherence in your TOK exposition.", "color": null, "status": "unread", "statusUpdatedAt": null, "statusUpdatedBy": null, "groupName": null}]}]}}, "rubricData": {"id": 57, "rubricId": "15a001d0-4b6b-41b6-abae-4e9498385eaf", "version": 1, "status": "published", "createdAt": "2025-02-20 06:03:43.512632+00", "totalMarks": 10, "description": null, "type": "TOK", "rubricSpecificInfo": null, "tags": [""], "isArchived": false, "gradeBoundaryId": "52ad2701-27bc-42f3-be3f-d63b98d98139", "name": "TOK Exhibition", "slug": "tok-exhibition", "rubricCriteria": [{"id": "cc70033e-f75e-42d2-8670-9501aa0d86a1", "rubricId": "15a001d0-4b6b-41b6-abae-4e9498385eaf", "revisionId": 57, "groupName": "TOK Exhibition", "label": null, "orderIndex": 0, "createdAt": "2025-02-20 06:03:55.358727+00", "updatedAt": "2025-07-16 11:21:18.828885+00", "isGradable": true, "showGradedScore": true, "isChecklistCriterion": false, "description": null, "rubricCriterionBands": [{"id": "9ff6a42c-458d-4ba2-aed7-d0ce052fc68b", "rubricCriterionId": "cc70033e-f75e-42d2-8670-9501aa0d86a1", "marksFrom": 0, "marksTo": 0, "orderIndex": 0, "createdAt": "2025-02-20 06:04:46.486581+00", "rubricCriterionStrandBandContents": [{"id": "f7cb0652-0737-403e-8f65-be13bd2fd7f1", "rubricCriterionStrandId": "17a30166-bc52-427b-904b-44efbdd5c7d7", "rubricCriterionBandId": "9ff6a42c-458d-4ba2-aed7-d0ce052fc68b", "content": "The exhibition does not reach the standard described by the other levels or does not use one of the IA prompts provided.", "createdAt": "2025-02-20 06:04:58.577216+00"}]}, {"id": "a1ba39dd-f4e1-46d0-92fb-f804616659df", "rubricCriterionId": "cc70033e-f75e-42d2-8670-9501aa0d86a1", "marksFrom": 1, "marksTo": 2, "orderIndex": 1, "createdAt": "2025-02-20 06:04:47.076074+00", "rubricCriterionStrandBandContents": [{"id": "861f06ce-2b51-46ce-a6ee-3022e7080288", "rubricCriterionStrandId": "17a30166-bc52-427b-904b-44efbdd5c7d7", "rubricCriterionBandId": "a1ba39dd-f4e1-46d0-92fb-f804616659df", "content": "The exhibition presents\nthree objects, but the\nreal-world contexts of\nthese objects are not\nstated, or the images\npresented may be\nhighly generic images of\ntypes of object rather\nthan of specific\nreal-world objects. Links\nbetween the objects\nand the selected IA\nprompt are made, but\nthese are minimal,\ntenuous, or it is not\nclear what the student is\ntrying to convey.\nThere is very little\njustification offered for\nthe inclusion of each\nobject in the exhibition.\nThe commentary on the\nobjects is highly\ndescriptive or consists\nonly of unsupported\nassertions.", "createdAt": "2025-02-20 06:05:04.443183+00"}]}, {"id": "d33f3613-07e3-4130-984c-f84b6431e3e4", "rubricCriterionId": "cc70033e-f75e-42d2-8670-9501aa0d86a1", "marksFrom": 3, "marksTo": 4, "orderIndex": 2, "createdAt": "2025-02-20 06:04:48.072006+00", "rubricCriterionStrandBandContents": [{"id": "e8acd337-a77d-4319-a744-06094151d57b", "rubricCriterionStrandId": "17a30166-bc52-427b-904b-44efbdd5c7d7", "rubricCriterionBandId": "d33f3613-07e3-4130-984c-f84b6431e3e4", "content": "The exhibition identifies three objects, although the real-world contexts of the objects may be implied rather than explicitly stated. Basic links between the objects and the selected IA prompt are made, but the explanation of these links is unconvincing and/or unfocused. There is a superficial justification for the inclusion of each object in the exhibition. Reasons for the inclusion of the objects are offered, but these are not supported by appropriate evidence and/or lack relevance to the selected IA prompt. There may be significant repetition across the justifications of the different objects", "createdAt": "2025-02-20 06:05:20.428881+00"}]}, {"id": "bd39c308-b52c-4662-b0f5-64d285be9e95", "rubricCriterionId": "cc70033e-f75e-42d2-8670-9501aa0d86a1", "marksFrom": 5, "marksTo": 6, "orderIndex": 3, "createdAt": "2025-02-20 06:04:48.868343+00", "rubricCriterionStrandBandContents": [{"id": "c257e18a-e3b8-46f4-b3b9-d9ea5cd5db84", "rubricCriterionStrandId": "17a30166-bc52-427b-904b-44efbdd5c7d7", "rubricCriterionBandId": "bd39c308-b52c-4662-b0f5-64d285be9e95", "content": "The exhibition identifies three objects, although the real-world contexts of these objects may be vaguely or imprecisely stated. There is some explanation of the links between the three objects and the selected IA prompt. There is some justification for the inclusion of each object in the exhibition. Some of the points are supported by evidence and references to the selected IA prompt.", "createdAt": "2025-02-20 06:05:31.312862+00"}]}, {"id": "48708361-8824-4c01-bcbd-39c3e493de8e", "rubricCriterionId": "cc70033e-f75e-42d2-8670-9501aa0d86a1", "marksFrom": 7, "marksTo": 8, "orderIndex": 4, "createdAt": "2025-02-20 06:04:49.555746+00", "rubricCriterionStrandBandContents": [{"id": "f16fe76e-abd8-4dc1-9a4f-50ab9e121c99", "rubricCriterionStrandId": "17a30166-bc52-427b-904b-44efbdd5c7d7", "rubricCriterionBandId": "48708361-8824-4c01-bcbd-39c3e493de8e", "content": "The exhibition identifies three objects and their real-world contexts. Links between each of the three objects and the selected IA prompt are explained, although this explanation may lack precision and clarity in parts. There is a justification of the contribution that each individual object makes to the exhibition. Many of the points are supported by appropriate evidence and references to the selected IA prompt.", "createdAt": "2025-02-20 06:05:40.123527+00"}]}, {"id": "5552e9fd-0d0a-4bb2-9ece-5e7a3c438771", "rubricCriterionId": "cc70033e-f75e-42d2-8670-9501aa0d86a1", "marksFrom": 9, "marksTo": 10, "orderIndex": 5, "createdAt": "2025-02-20 06:04:50.346899+00", "rubricCriterionStrandBandContents": [{"id": "055fe2ad-3ef1-4074-af44-83cc3440cc7a", "rubricCriterionStrandId": "17a30166-bc52-427b-904b-44efbdd5c7d7", "rubricCriterionBandId": "5552e9fd-0d0a-4bb2-9ece-5e7a3c438771", "content": "The exhibition clearly identifies three objects and their specific real-world contexts. Links between each of the three objects and the selected IA prompt are clearly made and well-explained. There is a strong justification of the particular contribution that each individual object makes to the exhibition. All, or nearly all, of the points are well-supported by appropriate evidence and explicit references to the selected IA prompt.", "createdAt": "2025-02-20 06:05:51.46084+00"}]}], "rubricCriterionStrands": [{"id": "17a30166-bc52-427b-904b-44efbdd5c7d7", "rubricCriterionId": "cc70033e-f75e-42d2-8670-9501aa0d86a1", "orderIndex": 0, "createdAt": "2025-02-20 06:03:59.452498+00", "name": "Does the exhibition successfully show how TOK manifests in the world around us?"}]}]}, "similarExemplars": [{"id": "e90f458b-2ab9-4e8c-b16e-c7f909736410", "title": "Can new Knowledge change established values and beliefs?", "description": "", "tags": ["grade-A", "tok", "sl"], "slug": "can-new-knowledge-change-established-values-and-beliefs", "isPublic": true, "isPremium": true, "showScores": true, "createdAt": "2025-08-05T08:04:05.381Z", "userSubmissionId": "81e433af-67d8-4ffa-9c81-146aa7fe8803", "submissionId": "33a64f5a-c657-494a-9e8f-d47cba7695ba", "similarity": 0.49362577999999996, "normalizedScore": 1, "compositeScore": 0.645538046, "matchingFileId": "", "matchingChunkId": "", "matchingChunkNumber": 0, "userSubmission": {"id": "81e433af-67d8-4ffa-9c81-146aa7fe8803", "score": "A", "scoreType": "letter", "level": null, "researchQuestion": null, "tokPrompt": null, "title": "Can new Knowledge change established values and beliefs?", "cohort": "M25", "createdAt": "2025-07-28T16:22:19.850Z", "subjectId": 582, "rubricId": "15a001d0-4b6b-41b6-abae-4e9498385eaf", "subject": {"id": 582, "title": "Theory of Knowledge (TOK)", "slug": "ib-theory-of-knowledge-tok"}, "rubric": {"id": "15a001d0-4b6b-41b6-abae-4e9498385eaf", "title": "TOK Exhibition", "type": "TOK"}, "totalRawMark": 9, "totalModeratedMark": 8}, "submission": {"id": "33a64f5a-c657-494a-9e8f-d47cba7695ba", "type": "TOK", "level": "SL", "createdAt": "2025-08-05T08:01:28.019Z", "files": [{"submiss